All the rarity does here is:
1. Probability of each trait converted into bits of information (literally called bit of information in information theory)
2. Add all of those together (mathematically better to add bits of info than probabilities)
3. Normalize based on # of traits for cross-collection comparison
4. Rank them 1 to 10000 based on this score

This means rank #1 is the least likely to have occurred.
And rank #10000 is the most likely to have occurred.
